<subSubSection id="C338650DFFDB997344D4FF58FC65F96A" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9D3686FFDB997344D4FF58FEF7FEB8" blockId="4.[136,1452,158,329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB997344D4FF58FD07FF48" bold="true" box="[189,651,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Distribution, habitat and phenology:—</emphasis>
This species is known only from Seasonally Dry Tropical Forests within Caatinga vegetation in the southern portion of 
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB997346FCFF04FC05FF2C" box="[661,905,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
Chapada 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D05FFDB9973476AFF05FC05FF2C" box="[771,905,195,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Diamantina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Diamantina</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49E6F864FFDB997347FEFF04FB97FF2C" box="[919,1051,194,220]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Bahia State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3357616FFDB9973404FFF04FBE2FF2C" box="[1062,1134,194,220]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The region surrounding the municipality of Rio de Contas is a known center of diversity within the 
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB997347CBFF20FB19FEF0" box="[930,1173,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
Chapada 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D05FFDB99734066FF21FB19FEF0" box="[1039,1173,231,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Diamantina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Diamantina</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and holds large numbers of endemic flowering plants (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B77FFDB997345B6FECCFDFCFED5" author="Harley, R. M." box="[479,624,266,293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" refId="ref3090" refString="Harley, R. M. (1995) Introduction. In: Stannard, B. L. (Ed.) Flora of the Pico das Almas, Chapada Diamantina, Bahia, Brasil. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew." type="book" year="1995">Harley 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B77FFDB99734617FECCFCD8FED4" author="Rapini, A. &amp; Ribeiro, P. L. &amp; Lambert, S. &amp; Pirani, J. R." box="[638,852,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" pagination="16 - 24" refId="ref3645" refString="Rapini, A., Ribeiro, P. L., Lambert, S. &amp; Pirani, J. R. (2008) A flora dos campos rupestres da Cadeia do Espinhac ¸ o. Megadiversidade 4: 16 - 24." type="journal article" year="2008">
Rapini 
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB997346BAFECDFC82FED4" box="[723,782,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). Flowering from April to September. Fruiting from August to September.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5D660EFFDB997344E1FA4EFB7EFA6E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5151440" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5151440" box="[136,1266,1416,1438]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5151440/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" startId="4.[136,229,1416,1438]" targetBox="[175,1424,400,1345]" targetPageId="4">
