<paragraph id="8B9D3686FFDB997344D4FA0AFC65F96A" blockId="4.[136,1452,1484,1979]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB997344D4FA0AFE35FA16" bold="true" box="[189,441,1484,1510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Conservation status:</emphasis>
—The first collection of 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D05FFDB9973468AFA0AFB90FA16" authorityName="R. F. Almeida &amp; Amorim" authorityYear="2014" box="[739,1052,1484,1510]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caatingicola">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB9973468AFA0AFB90FA16" box="[739,1052,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon caatingicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded two years after the publication of a taxonomic revision of the Neotropical species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D05FFDB99734716FA36FBADF9FA" box="[895,1057,1520,1546]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB99734716FA36FBADF9FA" box="[895,1057,1520,1546]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B77FFDB99734027FA36FA9EF9FA" author="Anderson, C. E." box="[1102,1298,1520,1546]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" pagination="1 - 313" refId="ref2845" refString="Anderson, C. E. (1997) Monograph of Stigmaphyllon (Malpighiaceae). Systematic Botany Monographs 51: 1 - 313. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 25027873" type="journal article" year="1997">Anderson (1997)</bibRefCitation>
. This species is represented by only a few records restricted to three municipalities within approximately 
<quantity id="4CDA9B63FFDB997340F5F9D2FB68F9DE" box="[1180,1252,1556,1582]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" unit="km" value="90.0">90 km</quantity>
of each other, all of them with anthropomorphically modified Caatinga vegetation. Thus, according to IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria (2012), this species should be regarded as Critically Endangered (categories B1a and B1b), due to its range of distribution being less than 
<quantity id="4CDA9B63FFDB997345D7F946FD9FF96A" box="[446,531,1664,1690]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" unit="km" value="100.0">100 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C579BCEFFDB9973467BF946FD96F97E" attach="left" box="[530,538,1664,1678]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">2</superScript>
and continually declining habitat quality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C338650DFFDB997344D4F962FB75F94E" box="[189,1273,1700,1727]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9D3686FFDB997344D4F962FB75F94E" blockId="4.[136,1452,1484,1979]" box="[189,1273,1700,1727]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB997344D4F962FEC4F94E" bold="true" box="[189,328,1700,1726]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet refers to its restricted distribution within Caatinga vegetation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C338650DFFDB997344D4F90EFB95F84A" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9D3686FFDB997344D4F90EFB95F84A" blockId="4.[136,1452,1484,1979]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB997344D4F90EFEC9F912" bold="true" box="[189,325,1736,1762]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Discussion:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D05FFDB99734508F90EFD18F912" authorityName="R. F. Almeida &amp; Amorim" authorityYear="2014" box="[353,660,1736,1762]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caatingicola">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB99734508F90EFD18F912" box="[353,660,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon caatingicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a distinctive leafless species when flowering, a character only known for 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D05FFDB997344D8F92AFD25F8F6" authority="Diels (1937: 101)" authorityName="Diels" authorityPageNumber="101" authorityYear="1937" box="[177,681,1772,1798]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nudiflorum">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB997344D8F92AFE5BF8F6" box="[177,471,1772,1798]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon nudiflorum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB34B77FFDB99734589F92AFD25F8F6" author="Diels, F. L. E." box="[480,681,1772,1798]" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" pagination="101" refId="ref3046" refString="Diels, F. L. E. (1937) Bibliotheca Botanica 29 (116): 101." type="journal article" year="1937">Diels (1937: 101)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F3357616FFDB99734699F92AFCC3F8F6" box="[752,847,1772,1798]" name="Ecuador" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and few other 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D05FFDB99734068F92AFB2AF8F6" authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[1025,1190,1772,1798]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Malpighiaceae</taxonomicName>
species as 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D05FFDB9973414EF92AFD7DF8DA" authority="(Griseb.) W. R. Anderson &amp; C. C. Davis (2006: 10)" authorityName="W. R. Anderson &amp; C. C. Davis" authorityPageNumber="10" authorityYear="2006" baseAuthorityName="Griseb." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Diplopterys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB9973414EF92AFF4CF8DA" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Diplopterys lutea</emphasis>
(Griseb.) W.R.Anderson &amp; C.C.Davis (2006: 10)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D05FFDB99734744F8D7FA08F8DB" authority="(Griseb.) Nied. (1928: 336)" authorityName="Nied." authorityPageNumber="336" authorityYear="1928" baseAuthorityName="Griseb." box="[813,1412,1808,1835]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Heteropterys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dumetorum">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB99734744F8D7FBCAF8DA" box="[813,1094,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Heteropterys dumetorum</emphasis>
(Griseb.) Nied. (1928: 336)
</taxonomicName>
. Its leaves are membranaceous, densely tomentose abaxially when young, and seem to grow right after fruit maturing. 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D05FFDB997344E1F89EFE32F882" authorityName="R. F. Almeida &amp; Amorim" authorityYear="2014" box="[136,446,1880,1906]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caatingicola">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB997344E1F89EFE32F882" box="[136,446,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon caatingicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be mistakenly misidentified as a Cerrado species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C224D05FFDB99734040F89EFF72F867" authority="A. Juss. (1833: 52)" authorityName="A. Juss." authorityPageNumber="52" authorityYear="1833" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malpighiaceae" genus="Stigmaphyllon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="86" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="urenifolium">
<emphasis id="B956EA94FFDB99734040F89EFAD9F882" box="[1065,1365,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Stigmaphyllon urenifolium</emphasis>
A.Juss. (1833: 52)
</taxonomicName>
, which also occurs within State of Bahia, and States of Minas Gerais and Mato Grosso do Sul. These species differ from each other mostly on leaf, gynoecium and fruit morphology (
<tableCitation id="C6A0033DFFDB997347DCF866FB84F84A" box="[949,1032,1952,1978]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[136,224,158,182]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of diagnostic morphological characters between S. caatingicola and S. urenifolium." pageId="4" pageNumber="86">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
